BaseField.Name: Label24
BaseField.Text: Instructions: This record is used to set up a set of regulations and pre-inspection tasks that are recommended for a given inspection. These templates should help inspectors to quickly start an inspection without needing to set it up.

BaseField.Name: Notify Provider
BaseField.AccessibilityLabel: Notify provider of schedule Field Required

BaseField.Name: Label40
BaseField.Text: This indicates that the inspections are unscheduled or the provider is not notified so the inspection is unannounced.

BaseField.Name: Label42
BaseField.Text: Instructions: Pre-Inspection Tasks are a list of items the Inspection Contact will be prompted for if activities need to be completed before the inspection occurs. If this template does not have any Pre-Inspection activities, you do not need to add any tasks here. If you have a pre-inspection, add those tasks below using the Add Pre-Inspection Task button. If you need to stop using a task, select the checkbox to the left and then select "Disable Selected" button. If you need to re-activate a task, follow the same steps but use the "Enable Selected" button.

BaseField.Name: Label45
BaseField.Text: Instructions: Select a regulation below and select Add Regulation button to add it to the template.

BaseField.Name: Label48
BaseField.Text: Instructions: Select a regulation in the list below and use "Disable Selected" button to Inactivate regulations if you don't want them used as part of the template any longer. Use "Enable Selected" to start using a regulation again with this template.

BaseField.Name: DataField8
BaseField.Text: Instructions: This section is only visible to VaultAccess users. Check Administrator Override to remove read-only configurations and show all fields. Select Admin Save to save any changes without applying business rules. Remember to uncheck override and save before closing.
